1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about Type Ia supernovae than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:11,600
These explosions occur in binary star systems when a white dwarf siphons material from its companion.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:14,400
Once it reaches a critical mass, boom!

4
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:17,600
A supernova erupts, shining brighter than entire galaxies.

5
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:23,200
Type Ia supernovae are crucial for measuring cosmic distances, acting as reliable 'standard candles'.

6
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:24,800
But there’s still uncertainty!

7
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,600
Variations in their brightness can puzzle scientists.

8
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,600
Curious about more cosmic mysteries?

9
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,600
